The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Pfizer net profit jumps

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Feb. 24: Pfizer Ltd has posted a 125 per cent rise in net profit for the quarter ended November 30 at Rs 13.71 crore against Rs 6.10 crore in the year-ago period.

 Total income increased modestly to Rs 149.32 crore from Rs 143.75 crore in the same period last year. 

 Pfizer said the scheme of amalgamation of erstwhile Pharmacia Healthcare Limited with the company was approved by Bombay High Court by its order on February 4. 

 In view of the approval, effective December 1, 2003, the audited figures for the year ended November 30, includes the figures of Pharmacia Healthcare. 

 Due to this, the audited figures for the year ended November 30 is not comparable with that of the previous periods, it added.

 For the year, the company has posted a net profit of Rs 45.52 crore compared with Rs 27.51 crore last year. Total income was placed at Rs 597.02 crore over Rs 515.16 crore. 




